==English==
===Etymology===
Latin, neuter gerundive of ''[[referre]]'' (to refer)
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''referendum'''  (plural: '''[[referenda]]''' or '''[[referendums]]''')
# a [[direct]] [[popular]] [[vote]] on a [[propose]]d [[law]] or [[constitutional]] [[amendment]]
# a [[note]] from a [[diplomat]] to his [[government]] [[request]]ing [[instruction]]s
